## Sequence Diagrams

### API Authentication Flow

<<mermaid>>
  sequenceDiagram
      participant U as User
      participant F as Frontend
      participant API as API Gateway
      participant AUTH as Auth Service
      participant DB as Database

      U->>F: Login Request
      F->>API: POST /auth/login
      API->>AUTH: Validate Credentials
      AUTH->>DB: Query User
      DB-->>AUTH: User Data
      AUTH-->>API: JWT Token
      API-->>F: Authentication Response
      F-->>U: Redirect to Dashboard

      Note over U,DB: Complete authentication flow
      Note over AUTH,DB: Secure validation

---

## UML Class Diagrams

### User Management System

<<mermaid>>
  classDiagram
      class User {
          +int id
          +string email
          +string name
          +Date createdAt
          +login()
          +logout()
          +updateProfile()
      }

      class Role {
          +int id
          +string name
          +string[] permissions
          +hasPermission()
      }

      class UserRole {
          +int userId
          +int roleId
          +Date assignedAt
      }

      User "1" --> "*" UserRole : has
      Role "1" --> "*" UserRole : assigned to

      class Profile {
          +int userId
          +string avatar
          +string bio
          +Date lastLogin
          +updateAvatar()
      }

      User "1" --> "1" Profile : owns

---

## State Diagrams

### Order Lifecycle

<<mermaid>>
  stateDiagram-v2
      [*] --> Created
      Created --> Pending : Validate
      Pending --> Processing : Approve
      Pending --> Cancelled : Reject
      Processing --> Shipped : Complete
      Processing --> Cancelled : Error
      Shipped --> Delivered : Confirm
      Delivered --> [*]
      Cancelled --> [*]

      note right of Created : Initial order state
      note left of Delivered : Successful final state

